# Supabase Client Usage

- In server components and API routes: use createServerClient from src/lib/supabase/server.ts
- In client components: use createBrowserClient from src/lib/supabase/client.ts
- Always use .select() to specify columns instead of select('*')
- Chain .order() for consistent ordering
- Use .single() when expecting exactly one row
- Handle errors: const { data, error } = await supabase.from(...); if (error) throw error;
- For file uploads: supabase.storage.from('bucket').upload(path, file, { upsert: true })
- For public URLs: supabase.storage.from('bucket').getPublicUrl(path)
